sql:
SELECT COUNT(lipid_id) AS lipid_count
FROM lipids
WHERE lipid_score >= 0.8;

SELECT AVG(retention_time) AS average_retention_time
FROM lipids
WHERE lipid_subclass = 'LPA' AND lipid_score > 0.8;

external_knowledge:
Notable intensity level refers to an average intensity greater than 100;
Typical strength of connection refers to the average link intensity;
The lipids are classified into various groups, with 'Fatty Acyls' being one of them.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT lipid_id) AS unique_lipids_count
FROM audit_trail
WHERE user_id = 'specific_user_id';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS lipid_count
FROM lipids
WHERE lipid_class = 'Fatty Acyl';

external_knowledge:
- Retention time between 10 and 20 seconds is the timeframe described metaphorically as the "chromatographic meadow".;
- Lipid classes are likened to types of butterflies to provide a metaphorical understanding.;
- More than five representatives implies a count greater than five for each lipid class.;

sql:
SELECT AVG(lipid_score) AS average_high_score
FROM lipids
WHERE lipid_score > (SELECT AVG(lipid_score) FROM lipids);

SELECT lipid_id, lipid_class, lipid_score
FROM lipids
ORDER BY lipid_score DESC;
